<HEADLINE> Surgery Planned for Co. Asst. Coach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Tom McMahon, Colorado's co-defensive
coordinator and secondary coach, was scheduled to have surgery
Wednesday to remove a cancerous tumor.
</P>
<P>
   McMahon was diagnosed with lung cancer in June. He has been
undergoing chemotherapy and radiation treatments since July.
</P>
<P>
   Co-defensive coordinator Vince Okruch will coach the secondary
in McMahon's absence, and Matt Russell will assume Okruch's role
with the outside linebackers. Colorado faces Washington on
Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
