<HEADLINE> Forbes in Dead Heat With Librarian  </HEADLINE>
By BETH J. HARPAZ
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Rep. Michael Forbes, a three-term incumbent who
switched to the Democrats last year, found himself in a virtual tie
Tuesday with a 71-year-old librarian.
</P>
<P>
   Regina Seltzer, who raised $40,000 to Forbes' $1.4 million, was
ahead by 39 votes of the 11,611 cast in unofficial returns. Forbes
said voting machines had been impounded for a recount that would
take several days.
</P>
<P>
   ''If my opponent is truly several dozen votes ahead, we're going
to support her and live by the will of the people,'' he said from
Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   Ninety minutes after the polls closed, Seltzer, who fought the
state Democratic Party's support of Forbes, crowed: ''At this point
I'm declaring victory.''
</P>
<P>
   Only two other incumbents have lost in primary elections this
year: Democrat Rep. Marty Martinez of California and GOP Rep.
Merrill Cook of Utah.
</P>
<P>
   Forbes switched parties last year after being wooed by Democrats
trying to reclaim House control. He was personally welcomed into
the party by President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   Seltzer said that with Forbes' opposition to abortion and votes
to impeach Clinton, he is no Democrat.
</P>
<P>
   Republicans couldn't wait until the fall. Their candidate, Felix
Grucci, was unopposed. The GOP sent mailings to Democrats gleefully
touting Forbes' 100 percent rating from the Christian Coalition.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mike Forbes is a goner,'' said Jim Wilkinson of the National
Republican Congressional Committee.
</P>
<P>
   Seltzer said her showing proved that local Democrats were not
happy about having a one-time Republican foisted on them.
</P>
<P>
   ''We can only conclude one thing: The people of Long Island, of
the first Congressional District, don't want to be told by
Washington, D.C., who is going to represent them,'' said Seltzer.
</P>
<P>
   Seltzer, a former school librarian, served on the Brookhaven
Town Council two decades ago and went to law school at age 50.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-13-00 0040 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
