</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Voters approved a half-percent sales tax to help the
Green Bay Packers renovate Lambeau Field, clearing the way for the team to start
construction in January. With 96 percent of Brown County's precincts reporting,
46,386 voters, or 53 percent, voted for the tax to raise $160 million for the
$295 million project. There were 40,947 votes against it. The county will start
collecting the tax Nov. 1, Packers president Bob Harlan said.
