<HEADLINE> Garcia, Still 49ers' Starting QB  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- Jeff Garcia will remain the San
Francisco 49ers' starting quarterback for at least another week.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Steve Mariucci said Tuesday night that Garcia will start
San Francisco's game at St. Louis on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Mariucci considered benching Garcia this week after he led just
one touchdown drive in the first three quarters of the 49ers' 38-22
loss to Carolina on Sunday. San Francisco fell to 0-2 with its
worst loss in a home opener since 1988.
</P>
<P>
   ''(Garcia) has given his all for the past year and has earned
his position as the starter,'' Mariucci said. ''We also are pleased
with the play of Rick Mirer, who has shown an ability to run the
offense when given the opportunity, but at this time, we feel that
Jeff is better prepared to start and play well.''
</P>
<P>
   Garcia, who was 12-of-20 for 181 yards and one interception, was
benched in the fourth quarter with the 49ers down 38-7. Mirer threw
for 126 yards and led San Francisco to two late touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   While Garcia's teammates have been noncommittal about the
quarterback shuffle, he said the offensive woes were the result of
team-wide execution problems.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't feel I've played so poorly that it deserves a
switch,'' Garcia said Monday. ''I feel that I've earned that
position, and I don't think there should be a change. ... It
bothers me that the door was left open.''
</P>
<P>
   Garcia started 10 games for San Francisco last year -- his first
in the NFL after five seasons in the Canadian Football League --
while Steve Young battled concussions. Mirer, signed as a free
agent in June, is playing for his fifth NFL team in eight seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Garcia's quarterback rating after two games is 89.4 --
seventh-best in the NFC -- and he was victimized by several dropped
passes on Sunday. Still, San Francisco converted just one of six
third-down situations against the Panthers with Garcia in the game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
