Jackson's throw sailed over the head of first baseman Ryan Klesko.
</P>
<P>
   San Diego closed to within 4-2 when Eric Owens led off the fifth
with a single, stole second and went to third when Petrick's throw
sailed into center field. Owens scored easily as Pierre allowed the
ball to bounce past him to the center-field fence.
</P>
<P>
   The Padres took a 1-0 lead on Magadan's RBI single in the first.
Notes: Yoshii is 5-0 in 10 career September starts with an ERA of
2.83. ... Cirillo set a career high with his 47th double. He had 46
doubles in 1996 and 1997 with Milwaukee. ... The Padres stole three
more bases, giving them nine steals in as many attempts in the two
games against Colorado. ... In his previous three starts, Clement
walked 30 batters. Clement leads the majors in walks allowed with
115.
</P>
