<HEADLINE> Actor Jeff Bridges Inspired by Dad  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- The memory of his late father was on Jeff Bridges'
mind when he prepared for his latest movie role as president of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
   At a Statehouse ceremony Tuesday, Bridges said he studied
Presidents Clinton, Lyndon B. Johnson and John F. Kennedy, as well
as former New York Gov. Mario Cuomo.
</P>
<P>
   But it was his father, actor Lloyd Bridges, who was an
inspiration.
</P>
<P>
   ''More than any of those folks was my father and also elements
of myself. My dad was a very gregarious guy and had a lot of joy he
brought to his work,'' Bridges said.
</P>
<P>
   The elder Bridges died in 1998 at age 85.
</P>
<P>
   His son was in Boston to present an award to the winner of the
Massachusetts Film Office's screenwriting competition: Kris
Johnson, 23, of Hopkinton.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson won for his screenplay, ''Written in Water,'' about a
boy who grows up in a funeral home. Johnson will now have a chance
to pitch his screenplay to Hollywood executives, in meetings
arranged by the film office.
</P>
</TEXT>
