<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 34; Nasdaq Drops 8  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell Wednesday on news of a merger
between two of the country's largest banks and continued
nervousness about third-quarter earnings.
</P>
<P>
   In early trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average fell 34.41 to 11,198.82.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also down.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was off 5.67 at 1,476.32 , and
the Nasdaq composite index declined 7.76 to 3,841.75.
</P>
<P>
   Before the market opened, Chase Manhattan Bank announced it was
acquiring J.P. Morgan for about $36 billion in stock.
</P>
<P>
   J.P. Morgan traded down $8.06 at $177.38 in early trading, after
weeks of its stock price inching upward on rumors that it was an
acquisition target. Chase Manhattan fell $2.88 to $49.63.
</P>
<P>
   Investors also continued to monitor corporate earnings
prospects.
</P>
<P>
   Although most businesses won't report results until next month,
some have already began hinting at what to expect. The market has
fallen into its pattern of rewarding those who deliver strong
profits and outlooks, and punishing those who don't.
</P>
<P>
   SCI Systems was off $16.56, or nearly 30 percent, at $39.38
after the electronics manufacturer said its quarterly results would
fall below expectations, because of seasonal weakness in demand for
its products.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Sherwin Williams dropped $2.06 to $21.81 after the
paint company said quarterly earnings would not meet Wall Street
expectations because of higher raw material costs and tough
competition.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a narrow margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 149.41 million
shares, compared with 130.38 million in the last session.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was off 1.32 at 531.11.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average was up 0.94 percent. In
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was down 1.69 percent,
Britain's FT-SE 100 fell 1.46 percent, and France's CAC-40 was off
1.48 percent.
</P>
