<HEADLINE> Errol Flynn's Island To Be Sold  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) -- An island once owned by the Hollywood
swashbuckler Errol Flynn is being sold by the Jamaican government.
</P>
<P>
   A company run by Jamaican and foreign investors will pay $2.75
million for lush, half-mile-long Navy Island, officials said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The sale includes a decaying resort that offers a nude beach and
snorkeling. The company said it will add restaurants, boutiques and
luxury villas.
</P>
<P>
   In December, the government said it planned to sell the island
to ''Officer and a Gentleman'' actor Louis Gossett Jr. for $3
million, but the deal fell through.
</P>
<P>
   Flynn died in 1959. The government acquired the island in 1997
from an auto dealer.
</P>
