<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-13 19:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus crash on route to Lincoln Tunnel brings morning rush to a crawl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WEEHAWKEN, N.J. (AP) - Twelve people were taken to hospitals
Wednesday after two buses crashed head-on in the express bus lane
leading to the Lincoln Tunnel, jamming morning rush-hour traffic,
the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey said.
</P>
<P>
   The crash happened just before 7 a.m. when an Olympia Trails bus
from New York left its lane, colliding with an NJ Transit bus
heading into New York, Port Authority spokesman Steve Coleman said.
</P>
<P>
   Olympia driver Sandra Girons, 33, of Union City, and NJ Transit
driver Jack Poventud, 42, of Paterson, and five passengers from
each bus were taken to hospitals, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Port Authority police interviewed the drivers but had not
concluded their investigation so the agency would not comment on
what led to the accident, Coleman said.
</P>
<P>
   NJ Transit spokeswoman Anna Farneski said her agency believes
the Olympia driver skidded on wet pavement into their oncoming bus
after braking to avoid an accident in which a car hit the rear of a
truck.
</P>
<P>
   Olympia manager Glen Behrens said, ''At this time, we're still
gathering information regarding the accident. We really can't tell
what happened.''
</P>
<P>
   Girons has been driving for Olympia for ''seven to eight
months,'' Behrens said. Asked whether she had any tickets or
violations, he said, ''We're still looking at all of that.''
</P>
<P>
   Poventud has been driving for NJ Transit for 17 years and has a
''spotless'' record, Farneski said.
</P>
<P>
   The drivers were taken to Jersey City Medical Center, where they
were initially listed in critical condition. Both had been upgraded
to fair condition by late afternoon, hospital spokeswoman Lynn
McFarlane said.
</P>
<P>
   Coleman said the accident happened on Interstate 495, about 1.5
miles past the tunnel.
</P>
<P>
   The wreckage was cleared about 9:30 a.m., allowing the tube
leading out of New York to reopen, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Delays persisted for about an hour, he said.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Port Authority: http://www.panyny.gov
</P>
<P>
   NJ Transit: http://www.njtransit.state.nj.us
</P>
<P>
   Olympia Trails: http://www.olympiabus.com
</P>
</TEXT>
