<HEADLINE> Husband charged in fatal stabbing of wife; four sought in shooting in nearby town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BALDWIN, N.Y. (AP) - A 22-year-old was critically injured by a
gunshot wound to the head during a home invasion at his family's
house in Baldwin on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Timothy Maxwell was awakened by a knock at the home around 10:25
a.m, according to Detective Sgt. Daniel Severin of the Nassau
County Homicide Squad.
</P>
<P>
   When he opened the door three or four males pushed into the
house and shot him in the head, Severin said.
</P>
<P>
   The assailants ran away; police said witnesses provided only
vague descriptions.
</P>
<P>
   The victim was airlifted to Nassau County Medical Center, where
he was listed in extremely critical condition.
</P>
<P>
   A few miles away, in North Massapequa, Nassau homicide
detectives charged Anthony Guido, 41, with second degree murder in
connection with the fatal stabbing of his wife, Barbara Guido, 32,
in their home early Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Anthony Guido was taken to the Nassau County Medical Center with
stab wounds to his stomach that appeared to be self-inflicted,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police responded to a call about a family disturbance at the
couple's house around 6:40 a.m.
</P>
