<DOCNO> APW20000913.0206 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-13 20:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Broncos' Griese Fond of Oakland  </HEADLINE>
By AARON J. LOPEZ
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- It's hard to imagine anyone having fond memories
of an environment consisting of flying batteries, spike-haired
enemies and expletive-laden insults.
</P>
<P>
   The rock-concert setting in Oakland suits Denver Broncos
quarterback Brian Griese just fine.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's kind of a carnival atmosphere. I enjoy it,'' Griese said
Wednesday as Denver prepared for Sunday's game against the Raiders.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know about everybody else, but it's fun to go in there
and see all the characters. Once you get on the field and out of
the reach of all the fans throwing things at you, you can actually
play ball.''
</P>
<P>
   Griese has another reason to appreciate life in Oakland. It is
the site of his first victory as a starter in the NFL.
</P>
<P>
   After a disastrous four-game losing streak to open last season,
Griese was benched in favor of Bubby Brister, who subsequently was
injured two days before the Oakland game.
</P>
<P>
   Griese completed 17 of 29 passes for 234 yards and one touchdown
in Denver's 16-13 victory.
</P>
<P>
   ''To that point in my career, that was the biggest win I'd ever
had,'' he said. ''I'm sure you all know how I felt after going 0-4.
I needed a win. There was no two ways about it. It wasn't pretty,
but we ended up getting it.''
</P>
<P>
   Griese appears more confident this year and his productivity
ranks among the league's best.
</P>
<P>
   His 120 quarterback rating is tops in the NFL, and Griese also
is second in touchdown passes (5) and fourth in passing yards
(575). He has yet to throw an interception.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our offense has been playing well and scoring points, so I
haven't had to force many things,'' he said. ''The game has really
been coming to me. Hopefully, down the road it will continue that
way.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
