<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tigers' Palmer Ejected, 4th Inning  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Detroit Tigers third baseman Dean Palmer was
ejected in the fourth inning Wednesday night for arguing a called
third strike by home plate umpire Chris Guccione.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer was called out on a 2-2 pitch from Chicago's Jim Parque
to end the inning. Palmer stared at Guccione, started to walk to
the dugout and then threw his helmet in disgust.
</P>
<P>
   Guccione signaled that Palmer was ejected and the third baseman
ran over to argue. Detroit manager Phil Garner stepped in to
separate the two, and third base coach Doug Mansolino had to
restrain Palmer.
</P>
<P>
   Detroit's Juan Gonzalez argued with Guccione over a called third
strike in the first inning.
</P>
</TEXT>
