<HEADLINE> Quotes from viewers of Wednesday's debate between Hillary Rodham Clinton and Rick Lazio </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ''Everybody who would like to slap her, raise your hand.'' -
Arthur Deruve, 66, of Yonkers, watching the debate at the Sons of
Italy Lodge in White Plains, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   ''He won by a mile. He put her on the spot with that soft money
pledge. She wanted to crawl into the nearest hole. It was
especially great because expectations for her were really high.'' -
James Cavanaugh, chairman of the Westchester County GOP Committee.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think that she did better than he did. She answered
questions without ducking them like he did. She tried to be
ladylike, intelligent, and bright, and she was.'' - John Burns Sr.,
former state Democratic chairman, 1965-1971.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think that Mrs. Clinton overall made a better showing. I
think she actually answered questions more directly. Mr. Lazio was
very evasive.'' - Craig Goldstein of New Paltz, N.Y., registered as
an Independent and undecided on who he will vote for.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think she's exceptionally bright. She's a far better debater
but she has a long way to go before she convinces me to vote for
her.'' - Phyllis Granat, an undecided voter from Manhasset, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think Hillary won. She has the specifics, she's got a plan,
Lazio was so vague. He would not touch anything Hillary said
because he had nothing. ... She stuck with her husband so she'll
stick to any promise she makes.'' - Jojie Sperrazza, 54, a Clinton
supporter from Amherst, N.Y.
</P>
</TEXT>
