<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-13 21:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Lions Player, Colo. AD Dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Thurman ''Fum'' McGraw, the former
Detroit Lions lineman and Colorado State athletic director, died
Wednesday of complications from a stroke. He was 73.
</P>
<P>
   McGraw played defensive tackle for Detroit from 1950-54, helping
the Lions to three NFL championships. He was an assistant coach
with Pittsburgh from 1958-62.
</P>
<P>
   McGraw played football at Colorado State, and also wrestled and
competed in track and field. His No. 48 is one of only two football
numbers retired by the school.
</P>
<P>
   Rams football coach Sonny Lubick called McGraw ''the heart and
soul'' of Colorado State football. The team will honor McGraw with
helmet decals, beginning with Saturday night's game at Arizona
State.
</P>
<P>
   University president Albert Yates called McGraw ''a legend and a
hero to many of us, a man of courage and character who dedicated
his life to helping young people through education and athletics.''
</P>
<P>
   When a knee injury ended his NFL career, McGraw returned to his
alma mater as wrestling coach in 1955 and assisted with the
football and track teams.
</P>
<P>
   After returning to the NFL as an assistant coach with
Pittsburgh, he became a campus administrator at Colorado State in
1962 and was promoted to assistant athletic director three years
later. He led drives to build the school's football stadium and
basketball arena.
</P>
<P>
   In 1970, McGraw became an NFL scout, but returned to Colorado
State six years later as athletic director, a post he held until
retiring in 1986.
</P>
<P>
   He was a fixture at the Colorado Rockies' spring training camp
and at Coors Field, and a close friend of Rockies owner Jerry
McMorris.
</P>
<P>
   McGraw was inducted into the Colorado Sports Hall of Fame, the
National Football Foundation and Hall of Fame and the National
Association of College Directors of Athletics Hall of Fame.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-13-00 2158 </TRAILER>
