<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-13 22:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saint Ballado Colt Tops Keeneland  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- A chestnut colt by Saint Ballado was
purchased for $850,000 on Wednesday, the top price during the third
session of the Keeneland September Yearling Sale.
</P>
<P>
   Keeneland sold 273 yearlings Wednesday for a total of
$31,700,500. The average price was $116,119 and the median price
was $85,000. A year ago in the third session, Keeneland sold 284
head for $27,996,500 with an average price of $98,579 and a median
of $67,500.
</P>
<P>
   Keeneland has sold 716 yearlings for $193,842,500 so far during
the 13-day auction. The average price is $270,730 and the median
price is $140,000. Last year, after the first three sessions,
Keeneland had sold 755 yearlings for $148,885,500 with an average
price of $197,199 and a median of $110,000.
</P>
<P>
   John C. Oxley won the bidding war for the Saint Ballado colt out
of Sunyata.
</P>
<P>
   ''We thought he was very good looking and had all the right
parts,'' said Oxley, who owns champion Beautiful Pleasure. ''He has
a very strong pedigree both on top and bottom and had the looks to
go along with it.''
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday's sale was modest compared to the first two days of
the auction, when several long-standing auction records were set.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-13-00 2213 </TRAILER>
