<HEADLINE> Calif. Brush Blazes Burn 4,500 Acres  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AGUA DULCE, Calif. (AP) -- Three wind-driven fires sent walls of
flame roaring over at least 4,500 acres of Southern California
brush Wednesday, destroying at least three homes and threatening
more than a dozen others.
</P>
<P>
   Fifteen homes were evacuated in the Agua Dulce area about 50
miles northeast of Los Angeles after the homes were destroyed. That
blaze had burned some 200 acres, while the two others were not
immediately threatening any homes.
</P>
<P>
   The blazes broke out during a second day of scorching
temperatures across Southern California.
</P>
</TEXT>
