<HEADLINE> Pregnant Woman Killed by Sweeper  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A pregnant woman was killed and her 4-year-old
daughter was injured when they were struck by a street sweeping
truck Wednesday in downtown Washington, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The 29-year-old woman, identified by police as Felietia Sorto,
was crossing 13th Street at N Street with her daughter and a
grocery cart when she was hit.
</P>
<P>
   The girl, Onis Morlenis-Arbaizn, and the cart were pulled into
the machine and ejected out of it. Sorto got caught up in the
sweeper's brushes and had to be pulled out by rescue workers.
Workers held up sheets around the sweeper during the rescue to
shield the gruesome process from onlookers.
</P>
<P>
   Sorto was pronounced dead at the scene. Her daughter was taken
to Children's Hospital with minor injuries and admitted for
observation.
</P>
<P>
   It was unclear how the accident occurred. The sweeper reaches a
top speed of only 20 mph.
</P>
</TEXT>
