<HEADLINE> Man Killed, Fires In Cop Station  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DANVILLE, Ill. (AP) -- A man was shot and killed by police
Wednesday after he crashed his vehicle into a police station and
opened fire.
</P>
<P>
   Stanley Shank, 59, drove his Jeep Cherokee along a pedestrian
walkway and into the doors of the Vermilion County public safety
building shortly before 1 p.m. He then began shooting from the
driver's side window, Sheriff Pat Hartshorn said.
</P>
<P>
   Shank was hit several times when three Danville police officers
returned fire. He was pronounced dead at a hospital later. No one
else was injured.
</P>
<P>
   Hartshorn said police do not know what prompted Shank's actions.
He said the department has had contact with Shank in the past, but
did not reveal details.
</P>
<P>
   The public safety building houses the county jail, sheriff's
department and city police department.
</P>
