<HEADLINE> Flame Thrower Wins in Del Mar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Flame Thrower edged Street Cry by a head
Wednesday in the $250,000 Del Mar Futurity, giving trainer Bob
Baffert his fifth straight victory in the race for 2-year-olds.
</P>
<P>
   Flame Thrower, the even-money favorite ridden by Jerry Bailey,
ran seven furlongs in 1:22, just two-fifths of a second off the
stakes record set by Forest Camp in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Flame Thrower paid $4, $2.80 and $2.10 for his third victory in
three career starts. Street Cry returned $3.40 and $2.40, and
Arabian Light paid $2.60 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Bought for $270,000 last April at the Ocala sale, Flame Thrower
earned $150,000 for the win, running the colt's earnings to
$268,200. Flame Thrower won a maiden race on July 26, then took the
Best Pal Stakes on Aug. 23.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert also saddled the winners of the Del Mar Futurity in
1996-99: Silver Charm, followed by Souvenir Copy, Worldy Manner and
Forest Camp.
</P>
<P>
   The trainer and Bailey also teamed to win Wednesday's supporting
feature on closing day of the Del Mar meeting, taking the $75,887
race with 1-5 favorite Chilukki, who won by five lengths.
</P>
</TEXT>
